messages.message:
They plan on having regular human review workflows. I think a separate queue is the most logical solution, although we might have duplicate results or something because we'd still want that result to be reviewed in the normal way I'd assume.

I have heard this from other customers before but not really put much thought into the specifics. Might be worth putting some brain power into @jack.robbins and we can pick the team's thoughts down the line to get feedback?

yeah this needs quite a bit more thought. I plan to work with @Siya in April & May on a redesign of the deployments configuration screen (https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/EPD-3556), so this could fit well with that.
